article.headline: Montgomery scores 21, propels Tech in first-half surge
article.linkText: Georgia Tech beats Army for eighth straight win
article.story:
ATLANTA -- Alex Montgomery scored 21 points and Deja Foster had 12 points and 14 rebounds to lead Georgia Tech (No. 24 AP) to a 76-47 victory over Army on Saturday.

Georgia Tech (13-2) also got 12 points from Sasha Goodblett and 11 from Brigitte Ardossi in winning its eighth straight game.

Erin Anthony led Army (6-7) with 26 points and seven rebounds.

Army trailed early but rallied to tie it at 17-all. Georgia Tech went on a 20-6 run fueled by 10 points from Montgomery to lead 37-23 at halftime.
